      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 412: `onOriginalMessageParsed` writes the result into the currently selected conversation rather than the conversation that requested parsing. If the user switches chats before parsing completes, the result is dropped or applied to the wrong model lookup, so toggling back can leave the original message blank until another parse is triggered. Track the originating conversation/account with the parse request, or include them in the parser signal and update that specific model.\\n```suggestion\\n// Example direction: pass conv/account through the async parse request\\nmessageParser_-\u003eparseOriginalMessage(accId, convId, msgId, msg, linkColor, backgroundColor);\\n// ... emit originalMessageParsed(accountId, convId, messageId, html)\\n```",
